Celebrating Women's History Month.

        =20
Dear Daniyah,

At Stanford GSB, we mark Women's History Month by spotlighting Amelia Farac=
o-Hadlock <https://www.linkedin.com/posts/stanford-graduate-school-of-busin=
ess_womenshistorymonth-activity-7443013350017568769-s4yh?utm_source=3Dshare=
&utm_medium=3Dmember_desktop&rcm=3DACoAAAam570BgmUsMMJMnJA127VDU0CXcaDwoAI&=
utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_so=
urce=3Dnew_propsect>, MBA '26, whose campaign leadership advances policies =
for women, families, and children. We also go inside the first-year Executi=
ve Challenge <https://www.gsb.stanford.edu/experience/news-history/lessons-=
leadership-2025-executive-challenge?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_conte=
nt=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect> to see how student=
s practice leadership they'll carry through the MBA Program and beyond.
HONORING WOMEN'S HISTORY MONTH AT STANFORD GSB=20

In recognition of Women's History Month, we profiled Amelia Faraco-Hadlock =
<https://www.linkedin.com/posts/stanford-graduate-school-of-business_womens=
historymonth-activity-7443013350017568769-s4yh?utm_source=3Dshare&utm_mediu=
m=3Dmember_desktop&rcm=3DACoAAAam570BgmUsMMJMnJA127VDU0CXcaDwoAI&utm_campai=
gn=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew=
_propsect>, MBA '26. She is a devoted public servant who is committed to en=
suring that opportunity is within reach for women and girls across every co=
mmunity.

READ MORE <https://www.linkedin.com/posts/stanford-graduate-school-of-busin=
ess_womenshistorymonth-activity-7443013350017568769-s4yh?utm_source=3Dshare=
&utm_medium=3Dmember_desktop&rcm=3DACoAAAam570BgmUsMMJMnJA127VDU0CXcaDwoAI&=
utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_so=
urce=3Dnew_propsect>
Start Local, Then Go Global

In this episode of the View From the Top podcast, Alibaba co-founder, Joe T=
sai, talks about growth, failed pitches, and the AI arms race.

LISTEN NOW <https://www.gsb.stanford.edu/insights/joe-tsai-says-start-local=
-then-go-global?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_mediu=
m=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect>



The Economic Intuition Behind Sports, Dating, and Getting a Job

In this podcast, Professor Paul Oyer discusses the economic intuition of pr=
o athletes, the parallels between dating and the job market, the AI-driven =
resurgence of professional networks, and why economics is the study of scar=
ce resources.

LISTEN NOW <https://www.gsb.stanford.edu/insights/economic-intuition-behind=
-sports-dating-getting-job?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar2=
6&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect>



Lessons in Leadership at the 2025 Executive ChallengeEvery year, first-year=
 MBA students at Stanford GSB participate in the Executive Challenge <https=
://www.gsb.stanford.edu/experience/learning/leadership/executive-challenge?=
utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_so=
urce=3Dnew_propsect>, the culminating event for the Leadership Labs <https:=
//www.gsb.stanford.edu/stanford-gsb-experience/learning/leadership/leadersh=
ip-labs?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demai=
l&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect> course. Part of the required curriculum for al=
l MBA students, the challenge is a GSB-wide, day-long event in which studen=
t squads role-play three business cases.

READ MORE <https://www.gsb.stanford.edu/experience/news-history/lessons-lea=
dership-2025-executive-challenge?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=
=3Dmar26&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect>
Why Surprises Catch Us Off Guard =E2=80=94 And How to Anticipate Them=20

Shifting between abstract and concrete thinking can help us prepare for une=
xpected events.

READ MORE <https://www.gsb.stanford.edu/insights/why-surprises-catch-us-gua=
rd-how-anticipate-them?utm_campaign=3Dmba_newsletter&utm_content=3Dmar26&ut=
m_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnew_propsect>
Nini Hamrick, MBA '20

